Package: mirBottleneck
Title: Pan-Cancer miRNA Regulatory Bottleneck Discovery and Survival Scoring
Version: 0.99.5
Authors@R: 
    person("Mark Barsoum", "Markarian",
           email = "mkm25@mail.aub.edu",
           role  = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = ""))
Description:
    mirBottleneck implements a dual-score framework for classifying microRNAs
    (miRNAs) into four regulatory archetypes based on their network-level
    behaviour across cancer transcriptomes. The Variance Suppression Score
    (VSS) quantifies a miRNA's ability to reduce variance in validated target
    genes; the Coherence Induction Score (CIS) measures whether a miRNA
    coordinates co-expression among its targets above chance. Together, VSS
    and CIS define four archetypes: Conductor (high VSS, high CIS), Silencer
    (high VSS, low CIS), Dual (low VSS, high CIS), and Weak (low VSS, low
    CIS). A weighted composite bottleneck score derived from archetype
    membership predicts overall survival across TCGA cancer types. The
    package provides a fully automated pipeline for any TCGA cohort via
    TCGAbiolinks, locked-model external validation utilities for ICGC and
    GEO datasets, pan-cancer batch execution across all 33 TCGA projects,
    transcriptome entropy analysis, TF activity estimation via DoRothEA and
    VIPER, immune deconvolution via the TIMER2 REST API, and
    publication-ready visualization functions.
